,"updated_at":"2021-11-17T15:12:16Z","closed_at":"2021-11-17T15:12:16Z","author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"I'm trying to setup diffgram with the provided `setup.py` script.\r\n\r\nI have created an Azure storage with the container and respective access rights, but when I insert the _Connection String_ into the `setup.py` it fails with:\r\n\r\n```\r\nPlease provide the Azure Container Name [Default is diffgram-storage]:\r\nTesting Connection...\r\n[OK] Connection To Azure Account\r\n[OK] Write Permissions\r\n[ERROR] Read Permissions\r\nError Connecting to Azure: Please check you have read permissions on the Azure container.\r\nDetails: Traceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"install.py\", line 143, in validate_azure_connection\r\n    account_key = client.credential.account_key\r\nAttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'account_key'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe code where it fails looks like this:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nclient = BlobServiceClient.from_connection_string(connection_string)\r\n...\r\nshared_access_signature = BlobSharedAccessSignature(\r\n                account_name = client.account_name,\r\n                account_key = client.credential.account_key\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis makes little sense to me, as the connection_string already includes a SharedAccessSignature that can be used for reading the storage.\r\n\r\n**Suggestion**: Use `blob_client.download_blob()` method to download the test file.\r\n\r\nWhen skipping the test, the installation works.","closed_by":{"login":"tkupek","id":4039384,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQwMzkzODQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4039384?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tkupek","html_url":"https://github.com/tkupek","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tkupek/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tkupek/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tkupek/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.gith